────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

3A. MARKER TYPES

────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

  🔑 EXTRACT — defines WHERE to capture a dynamic value and HOW.

  Appears on the SOURCE request (the request whose response contains the value).

  Example from input:

    🔑 EXTRACT: ${Set_Cookie} ← response.headers.Set-Cookie [cookie[ASP.NET_SessionId]]

               Regex Extractor (response header Set-Cookie): ASP\.NET_SessionId=([^;]+)

  Fields to parse from each 🔑 EXTRACT block:

    - Variable name : e.g., Set_Cookie

    - Source field : "response.headers" → useHeaders = true

                        "response.body" → useHeaders = false

    - Regex pattern : the regex string after the colon, e.g., ASP\.NET_SessionId=([^;]+)

    - Reference name : same as variable name (without ${})

  ⚡ PARAM — defines WHERE a captured variable is USED in downstream requests.

  Appears on requests AFTER the source. The Agent uses ⚡ PARAM to replace literal

  captured values with ${Variable} references in:

    - Path

    - QParams values

    - Headers values (Cookie, Referer, Origin, etc.)

    - Request bodies

