ASSIGN TO UDV IF:

  Infrastructure/environment-related (PROTOCOL, SERVER, PORT)

  Execution controls (THREADS, RAMPUP, LOOPS)

  Static base URL or server name

  Value appears consistently across most requests

ASSIGN TO CSV DATA SET CONFIG IF:

  Test data that should vary per user (credentials, entity IDs, session tokens, timestamps)

DO NOT PARAMETERIZE (keep as literals in samplers):

  Request-specific paths

  Request-specific headers (Referer, Content-Type, X-NewRelic-ID, etc.)

  Request-specific query parameters

  Request bodies

  Static resource paths (.js, .css, .png)

Conflict Resolution:

  Varies per virtual user/iteration? → CSV

  Same for entire test run? → UDV

  Captured dynamically at runtime? → RegexExtractor (correlation variable)

  Specific to one request? → Literal in sampler

  Uncertain? → Keep as literal (safest)

